latestIgtvVideos.caption: Today is #WorldGiraffeDay! The longest day of the year honors the planet’s tallest animals, who are on the rebound from near extinction thanks to @giraffe_conservation—the non-profit’s brilliant translocation projects are slowly turning dwindling numbers around across Africa, which is hugely exciting! To celebrate, we created our exclusive Giraffe Beauty Set. Packaged in a chic giraffe pouch, it contains Luminescent Eye Shade in Giraffe, Nano Gold Energizing Eye Serum, and the Shade and Sweep Brush. 🦒🦒🦒 #Chantecaille #StandTallForGiraffe
To our own dear Olivier, and all the fathers in our Chantecaille family, we’re wishing you a joyful #FathersDay!

This #FathersDay, we are saluting all our conservation partners who also happen to be dads, including Olivier Nsengimana, a veterinarian and director of  Rwanda Wildlife Conservation Association. Olivier has waged a singular battle on behalf of the Grey Crowned Crane in his home country of Rwanda. We created our Luminescent Eye Shade in Crane to support his work, learn more on today’s Instagram Story. #Chantecaille

Reef-safe SeaScreen 30 Mineral Broad-Spectrum Sunscreen Mist SPF 30 gives back to @WildAid Marine + is packed with non-nano zinc to protect against sun damage without damaging fragile coral reefs. It gets a luxurious skincare boost from 8 organic botanicals, including Ashwagandha Root Extract and Wild Moss Rose. It’s a super-soothing shield for a day in the sun! ☀️ #Chantecaille

We created our reef-safe SeaScreen to support @WildAid Marine and their protection of coral reefs and marine wildlife in Tanzania's Pemba Channel Conservation Area — one of the largest protected areas in the region. It is home to several endangered species including sea turtles, dolphins, sharks, oceanic manta rays, and houses key sea turtle nesting sites. “It has been a long time since I’ve seen a thriving coral reef. That’s why I am thrilled that WildAid Marine and their partner, Coastal Community Conservation Zanzibar, are working tirelessly to achieve effective marine surveillance—it is so essential for the survival of marine wildlife. I hope to visit the Pemba reef very soon.” - @OliviaChantecaille 
 
#WorldOceansDay #Chantecaille

Awaken your #summer glow with Radiance Elixir. ✨This illuminating serum is infused with Skin-Awakening and Crystal Peptides that leave skin looking healthy, glowy, and fresh. Apply directly to clean skin or add a drop or two to your moisturizer or foundation for a luminous finish. #Chantecaille

Curated with sunny days in mind, @OliviaChantecaille’s Obsessions Surprise Box is a collection of must-have makeup and skincare delights – including Purifying and Exfoliating Phytoactive Solution, a botanical toning treatment. The limited edition box also features a fun summer surprise! #Chantecaille
Summer is coming! Stay tuned for tomorrow. “Inspired by flares of pure, brilliant sunlight that boost your mood and feed the soul.” - Creative Director @OliviaChantecaille

Build your dream lip look with our buy 3, take 20% off lips event! Choose a liner, lipstick and gloss combo or line up your ideal nude, red, and berry hues for the ultimate lip wardrobe. Use code LIPLOOKS at checkout. #Chantecaille

This month we’re celebrating our beloved #RosedeMai collection and the precious bloom that brings it to life. Read about how Sylvie discovered this unique French rose growing in a field in Grasse on Le Magazine (link in bio). #Chantecaille

Ready for an insta-lift? NEW Rose de Mai Eye Lift is designed with a unique Zamac applicator that acts as a cooling massage tool to instantly reduce the look of puffiness and dark circles. The silky serum is infused with lifting botanicals to visibly smooth and refresh the entire eye area, leaving it awake and radiant-looking. #Chantecaille

For the perfect rosy cheek sweep on NEW HD Radiant Blush. 🌸 Packaged with a mess-free flow-through brush, this buildable formula features smoothing ingredients that creates a silky feel and blurs the skin for a filtered effect. #Chantecaille

latestPosts.caption:
The Great Elephant Migration, led by our amazing partners @elephantfamily, has reached its final destination after a 5,000-mile journey across the U.S.!

This powerful public art initiative brought 100 hand-carved elephant sculptures crafted in Southern India to spark global conversations around conservation and coexistence.

Our CMO, Julia Frankenberger, joined the tour, traveling from Jackson Hole to Beverly Hills, connecting with inspiring leaders and celebrating our Beauty with Impact mission.

Stay tuned next month as we visit the Migration in Beverly Hills to unveil something very special!
